<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[192,1440,1607,1665]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,371,1607,1631]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Distribution.</emphasis>
Originally described from the Florida Keys, Grand Bahama, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1248,1607,1631]" name="Belize" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Belize</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; B. Landry" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="62 - 70" refId="ref20664" refString="Matthews, D. L., and B. Landry. 2008. Description of a new species of Exelastis (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae) from the neotropics, with keys to adults of the four species occurring in Florida. Tropical Lepidoptera Research 18 (2): 62 - 70." type="journal article" year="2008">Matthews and Landry 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution now also includes South Abaco Island.
</paragraph>
